President Obama held a meeting with Senators Tom Harkin, Mike Enzi, Jeff Bingaman, and Lamar Alexander to discuss the reauthorization of the Elementary and Secondary Education Act. The President emphasized the importance of education in shaping the nation's economic future. He expressed his desire to redefine the federal role in education to be more flexible and focused on responsibility, reform, and results. The President discussed raising expectations for students and schools, improving teacher effectiveness, and providing greater flexibility to support innovation and improvements in public education. He also mentioned the importance of initiatives like Race to the Top and providing incentives and rewards to help students succeed. Representatives John Kline, George Miller, Duncan Hunter, and Dale Kildee had to leave the meeting before it began due to a vote in Congress.